1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:06,036
Kafka guarantees ordering within a partition , but not across partitions.

2
00:00:05,986 --> 00:00:19,986
This is a critical design constraint: if you need all events for a given entity (e.g., a user) to be processed in order, all those events must land in the same partition.

3
00:00:19,986 --> 00:00:29,473
I watched a candidate explain this perfectly and get a 45 LPA offer at a top product company in Bangalore.

